**Liam's Code**

```c
#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>
#include <string.h>

int main() {
    // Initialize variables
    char buffer[1024];
    int port = 8080;
    int ip = 192.168.1.1;

    // Connect to the alien's surveillance system
    int sock = socket(AF_INET, SOCK_STREAM, 0);
    struct sockaddr_in addr;
    addr.sin_family = AF_INET;
    addr.sin_port = htons(port);
    inet_pton(AF_INET, ip, &addr.sin_addr);

    // Send a message to the system
    char *msg = "Hello, world!";
    send(sock, msg, strlen(msg), 0);

    // Receive a response from the system
    int len = recv(sock, buffer, 1024, 0);
    printf("%s\n", buffer);

    return 0;
}
```

The code is a simple program that connects to the alien's surveillance system and sends a message. It is a starting point, but it is far from complete.
